  <brief_title>Prevention of Umbilical Port-site Hernia After Laparoscopic Cholecystectomy Using a Prosthetic Mesh Versus Simple Suture</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hospital General Universitario Elche</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hospital General Universitario Elche</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <authority>Spain: Ethics Committee</authority>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The incidence of port-site hernia in patients with risk factors (obesity, elderly, diabetes
      and lung disorders) can be reduced by the use of a prophylactic mesh in the closure of
      umbilical port site.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <overall_status>Completed</overall_status>
  <start_date>January 2011</start_date>
  <completion_date type="Actual">December 2012</completion_date>
  <primary_completion_date type="Actual">December 2012</primary_completion_date>
  <phase>Phase 3</phase>
  <study_type>Interventional</study_type>
  <study_design>Allocation: Randomized, Endpoint Classification: Safety/Efficacy Study, Intervention Model: Parallel Assignment, Masking: Single Blind (Subject), Primary Purpose: Prevention</study_design>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Incidence of port-site hernia</measure>
    <time_frame>12 months</time_frame>
    <safety_issue>Yes</safety_issue>
    <description>Comparison of incidence of port-site hernia between patiensts with and without prophylactic mesh placement</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Postoperative pain</measure>
    <time_frame>12 months</time_frame>
    <safety_issue>Yes</safety_issue>
    <description>Evaluation of different pain perception in patients with and without prophylactic mesh placement, determined in the postoperative course and at 1, 6 and 12 months after surgery</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
